e:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Kissflow is best suited for mid market companies, process owners, HR teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Rossum, meanwhile, shines for enterprises, logistics, supply chain, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2012, Kissflow describes itself as \"Low-code work platform for process automation and project management.\" Rossum, established in 2017, positions itself as \"AI document understanding platform for enterprise data capture.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
f:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Rossum** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more features (10 vs 9). However, this does not mean Kissflow is a poor choice — far from it. Kissflow excels in its own right, particularly for mid market companies and process owners.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value high accuracy on structured documents, go with Rossum. If combines workflow and project management matters more to you, Kissflow is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
